Package src

Class Enrollment

java.lang.Object
src.Enrollment
public class Enrollment
extends java.lang.Object
This class contains a list of EnrollStudents or students enrolled for the current semester. The corresponding methods and interactions with the specific EnrollStudents are also included.
Author:
Christian Osma, Liam Smith

    • find

      private int find​(EnrollStudent student)
      This method takes an student and loops through the list to find the student. Should return the index of the student or -1 if the student is not in the list.
      Parameters:
      student - Student to be found in the list
      Returns:
      Integer representing the index of the Student in the list or -1 if not found.

    • add

      public void add​(EnrollStudent enrollStudent)
      This method takes an student as a parameter and adds it to the end of the list.
      Parameters:
      enrollStudent - The Student to be added to the enrollment list.

    • grow

      private void grow()
      Method that creates a new list that has four more elements than the current array. Then the method copies all students into the new list.

    • remove

      public void remove​(EnrollStudent enrollStudent)
      This method takes the student to be removed and swaps it with the student in the end of the list. Then, the end of the list is removed. If the student is not found, the method does nothing.
      Parameters:
      enrollStudent - Student to be removed from the list.

    • contains

      public boolean contains​(EnrollStudent enrollStudent)
      This method checks whether the passed in student is enrolled and returns a boolean value.
      Parameters:
      enrollStudent - The student to be found in the list.
      Returns:
      true if the student is in the enrollment list and false if it is not.

    • print

      public void print()
      This method loops through the enrollment list and prints out every student in standard output.

      This method finds the student in the enrollment list and changes their enrolled credits to the inputted value.
      Parameters:
      student - Student who needs their credits changed
      credits - Credits that the student is enrolled in
